"I wanted high ceilings, big windows, and lots of light.
That was my condition".
To this end, Notting Hill-based architecture and design studio Duck & Shed hired Erfan Azadi to take advantage of the 12.5 ft ceiling and create not only a structure but also a place for Joanne to live.
