Erfan had to think creatively to solve the problem.
"The steel skeleton is quite complex", he explains.
"We had to arrange the spaces so that they could be piled up without having to bend down on top of each other.
It wasn't just building a simple platform, but the steel would be tilted so that it would be at the right height for the function above or below".
This arrangement brought in many additional dramas, allowing Erfan to get two full-size rooms on top of each other.
