Eric Chaisse, an expert at the Provence-based agricultural research institute CRIEPPAM, said: "The lavender in Provence is effectively endangered because in recent years the plant has been exposed to the effects of climate change, which brings much less rain in the spring and mostly in the fall.
This affects the life of the lavender.
There is also a small leaf beetle, the August beetle, which is a pest that carries micro-bugs, and it is very abundant in very dry air".
And a lot of things are at stake.
